[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    374[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon API Gateway and Amazon Cognito for the plan-review API.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The clinical-team plan-review surface is exposed as an authenticated API consumed by the EHR integration layer (typically a SMART on FHIR app). API Gateway provides the endpoint, Cognito (or the institution's identity provider via SAML or OIDC) provides authentication, and per-clinician audit logs go to CloudTrail. The patient-facing plan delivery uses the institution's existing patient portal (Amazon Pinpoint or the EHR's patient-portal infrastructure for the channel layer); the API Gateway endpoint is for the clinician review surface.[K
